text.section:
An applicant for a school bus endorsement shall satisfy the following requirements:
Qualify for a passenger vehicle endorsement by passing the knowledge and skills test for obtaining a passenger vehicle endorsement;
Demonstrate knowledge of loading and unloading children, including the safe operation of stop signal devices, external mirror systems, flashing lights, and other warning and safety devices required for school buses by state or federal law or regulation;
Demonstrate knowledge of emergency exits and procedures for safely evacuating passengers in an emergency;
Demonstrate knowledge of state and federal laws and regulations related to safely traversing highway rail grade crossings; and
Submit to an annual physical examination in accordance with 49 C.F.R. pt. 391, completed by a medical examiner as defined by 49 C.F.R. pt. 390.
